          {
            "commit": "0e15e14373dba34de4888988cea95836e53bae04",
            "subject": "LU-13011 wbc: data on PCC for lock keep flush mode"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Qian Yingjin",
          "email": "qian@ddn.com",
          "date": "2021-08-20 02:10:33.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Qian Yingjin",
          "email": "qian@ddn.com",
          "date": "2021-08-20 02:10:33.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-13044 wbc: delay file removal for keep flush mode",
        "message": "LU-13044 wbc: delay file removal for keep flush mode\n\nIn (lazy or aging) lock keep flush mode, to optimize the file\nremoval performance, it can delay to perform the removal on\nbackground via the kernel flusher instead of the previous removal\nstrategy in synchronous way.\n\nThe general design is as follows:\n- Each directory in (C) state maintains a list L for removed\n  files. when deleting a children file under this directory, if\n  the file has been flushed (F), add it into the list L, and the\n  directory is marked as dirty. Then the file is deleted from\n  MemFS (not delete from the main Lustre file system right now).\n- When deleting a directory in (C) state, if its parent directory\n  is also in (C) state, it can splice the two removed file lists\n  into its parent's; If not in (C) state, it must synchronize to\n  delete the files and directories in the list to the server.\n- When the background flusher wakes up and it will check whether\n  L is empty for the dirty directory. If not, the files in L will\n  be deleted in batches accroding to the file FID;\n\nSigned-off-by: Qian Yingjin <qian@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: Icb12bf26938d8880c4bf77db9fbb51e79fa0e3c6\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
